<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[102134]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA["Perduts a la viquipèdia", at the Romea Theatre]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Theatre.</strong>A theatrical production starring children and adults who will  help us see the world from a scientific viewpoint.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Family and scientific theatre go well together in this theatrical production in which children and adults are the stars, helping us see the world from a scientific viewpoint.</p>
<p>Ada and Jaume are not keen on doing the project their teacher asked them to do about a scientist of their choice. The computer crashes to the floor and out comes Albert Einstein himself, chasing Neutrí, a tiny elementary particle that takes them inside Viquipèdia! There they meet the Curies, Monturiol, Leonardo Da Vinci, Watt, Faraday and many others who will help them return home using scientific methods. Ada and Jaume return from this marvellous scientific adventure completely transformed.</p>
